# Admin layout scroll containment

Evidence: BUG-2026-07-02 — sidebar scrolled away on long pages when outer shell used `min-h-screen`.

Desktop admin shells with a persistent left sidebar must **not** let the document body scroll past the sidebar.

## Required pattern

```tsx
// Root — lock to viewport; no document scroll
<div className="flex h-screen overflow-hidden" data-testid="admin-layout">
  <aside className="... md:h-screen md:shrink-0 ..." data-testid="admin-sidebar" />
  <div className="flex min-h-0 flex-1 flex-col overflow-hidden">
    <main className="min-h-0 flex-1 overflow-auto" data-testid="admin-main">
```

## Rules

1. **Root shell:** `h-screen overflow-hidden` (not `min-h-screen` alone).
2. **Scroll column:** `min-h-0` on flex children between root and `main` — required for `overflow-auto` to work in nested flex.
3. **Sidebar:** `md:h-screen md:shrink-0` so it stays full-height and does not compress.
4. **Only `main` scrolls** — sidebar/header chrome stay fixed while content scrolls.

## Regression guard

`apps/data-management-frontend/src/test/test_bug_2026_07_02_admin_sidebar_scroll.test.tsx`

When changing `AdminLayout` or similar admin shells, run that test (or extend it) before merge.
